IHP 130 nm EM/IR showcase — outputs license note
=================================================

What this repository is
-----------------------
This repository contains OUTPUT ARTIFACTS ONLY: the before/after EM/IR reports,
per-rectangle heat maps, comparison tables, and READMEs for two analog cells
rebuilt in IHP's open 130 nm process (sg13g2). These outputs are shareable — you
may view, copy, and redistribute the artifacts and tables in this repository for
evaluation and discussion, with attribution to Si-Hive.

What this repository is NOT
---------------------------
The tools that PRODUCE these artifacts are NOT included here:

  - the EM/IR analysis engine ("emirtool") — its extractor, IR nodal solver,
    EM screen, repair-directive schema, and tech packs; and
  - the CAL analog layout engine that builds and repairs the cells.

Neither engine's source is part of this repository. This repo is a results
showcase, not the engine.

Provenance
----------
ihp130 EM limits are the foundry's own DCCURRENTDENSITY values, parsed from the
IHP sg13g2 vendor tech LEF; results screened against them are signoff-grade (not
estimates). The DualCtrlVCO result is a real, DRC/LVS-clean run (2026-07-14); no
number in this repository is fabricated, estimated, or projected. Two figures are
explicitly labeled rather than silently claimed: the supply current is reused from
the identical sky130 sizing (not a fresh sg13g2 measure), and the AC decoupling MIM
caps are omitted (no DC current — the DC EM/IR screen is unaffected).

